<p>Hence, $C_n^* = C_{-n}$.</p>

<p>Now, let’s summarize our findings for this chapter. We re-wrote our Fourier Series in complex form, such that:</p>

<p><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mpadded width="+6pt" height="+6pt" lspace="3pt" voffset="3pt" style="border: 0.04em solid red" mathbackground="white"><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∞</mi></munderover><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mi>cos</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">]</mo><mspace linebreak="newline"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∞</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">∞</mi></munderover><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><msub><mi>ω</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>n</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mstyle></mstyle></mstyle></mpadded></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">
\fcolorbox{red}{white}{$f(t) = \frac{a_0}{2} + \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}[ a_n \cos(\frac{2\pi nt}{T}) + b_n \sin(\frac{2\pi nt}{T})] \\
= \displaystyle\sum_{n=-\infty}^{\infty}[ C_n (e^{i \omega_0 nt})]$}
